## 4. Understanding File Paths

A file path identifies where a file exists.

Windows example:

```text
C:\Users\Ali\Projects\data\students.csv
```

Linux or macOS example:

```text
/home/ali/projects/data/students.csv
```

Hardcoding complete paths makes code difficult to move between systems.

Problematic:

```python
file_path = "C:\\Users\\Ali\\Desktop\\students.csv"
```

Better:

```python
from pathlib import Path


file_path = Path("data") / "students.csv"
```

`pathlib` handles path separators across operating systems.

