## 9. Context Managers

This structure:

```python
with file_path.open(...) as file:
```

creates a context manager.

It automatically closes the file when the block finishes.

Visual explanation:

```text
Enter with block
      |
      v
File opens
      |
      v
Read or write
      |
      v
Block ends
      |
      v
File closes automatically
```

Without a context manager:

```python
file = open("notes.txt", "r")
content = file.read()
file.close()
```

This can fail to close the file if an error occurs before `close()`.

Use context managers for normal file operations.

