## 28. Handling File Errors

Common exceptions include:

```text
FileNotFoundError
PermissionError
IsADirectoryError
UnicodeDecodeError
json.JSONDecodeError
ValueError
```

Example:

```python
from pathlib import Path


file_path = Path("data/students.csv")

try:
    content = file_path.read_text(
        encoding="utf-8"
    )
except FileNotFoundError:
    print(
        f"File was not found: {file_path}"
    )
except PermissionError:
    print(
        f"Permission denied: {file_path}"
    )
```

Do not catch every exception and ignore it.

Bad:

```python
try:
    content = file_path.read_text()
except Exception:
    pass
```

This hides the real problem.

