## 33. Mathematical Intuition

Suppose the raw file contains:

[
R = 1000
]

rows.

After cleaning:

[
C = 920
]

rows remain.

Removed rows:

[
D = R - C
]

[
D = 1000 - 920 = 80
]

Removal percentage:

[
\text{Removal percentage}
=========================

\frac{D}{R}
\times 100
]

# [

\frac{80}{1000}
\times 100
==========

8%
]

A high removal percentage may indicate:

* Poor source data
* Cleaning rules that are too strict
* Incorrect assumptions
* Parsing problems

