## 35. Time Complexity

Let:

* (n) = number of rows
* (m) = number of columns
* (s) = file size

Reading the CSV:

[
O(s)
]

Validating columns:

[
O(m)
]

Converting and validating rows:

[
O(n)
]

Removing duplicate IDs:

[
O(n)
]

Writing cleaned data:

[
O(nm)
]

For a fixed number of columns, the pipeline is approximately:

[
\boxed{O(n)}
]

Memory usage is approximately:

[
\boxed{O(nm)}
]

because the DataFrame is loaded into memory.

