## 40. Mini Project: Multi-File Sales Consolidator

Directory:

```text
data/sales/
├── january.csv
├── february.csv
├── march.csv
└── notes.txt
```

Each CSV contains:

```text
order_id
product
quantity
unit_price
region
```

### Requirements

1. Find all CSV files using `glob()`.
2. Ignore non-CSV files.
3. Load every CSV.
4. Add a `source_file` column.
5. Validate required columns.
6. Convert quantity and price to numeric.
7. Remove invalid rows.
8. Combine all files.
9. Calculate:

[
\text{Revenue}
==============

\text{Quantity}
\times
\text{Unit Price}
]

10. Save the combined dataset.
11. Save JSON metadata containing:

    * Number of input files
    * Raw row count
    * Clean row count
    * Total revenue
12. Add unit tests.
13. Document errors without stopping the entire pipeline when one optional file is malformed.

Architecture:

```text
Sales directory
      |
      v
Find CSV files
      |
      v
Load each file
      |
      v
Validate and clean
      |
      v
Combine DataFrames
      |
      v
Calculate revenue
      |
      +----------------------+
      |                      |
      v                      v
Combined CSV             JSON summary
```

